<emphasis box="[151,429,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Oligoryzomys destructor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="60" pageNumber="61" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="60.[151,1437,1440,1719]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">
Karyotype: 2n = 60 and FN = 76. Autosomal complement: nine metacentric and submetacentric pairs (two large and seven medium to small), and 20 acrocentric pairs (one large and the remaining small). Sex chromosomes: X, a large submetacentric; Y, a medium metacentric (
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L." box="[752,1021,1548,1575]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref67114" refString="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L. (1976) Karyotypic variation in Oryzomyine rodents (Cricetinae) with comments on chromosomal evolution in the Neotropical Cricetine complex. Occasional papers of the Museum of Zoology, 49, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1976">Gardner &amp; Patton 1976</bibRefCitation>
, pp. 8, 
<figureCitation box="[1105,1195,1548,1574]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1948,1972]" captionTargetBox="[159,1427,1037,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-431@13.[151,1436,1029,1925]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution of diploid and fundamental number of karyotyped specimens of genus Euryoryzomys. (■) E. emmonsae; (□) E. lamia; (▲) E. macconnelli; (○) E. nitidus; (l) E. russatus; (r) Euryoryzomys sp. nov.; (ê) Euryoryzomys sp.." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423621" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423621/files/figure.png" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). This karyotype was referred as belonging to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tschudi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[426,575,1584,1611]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="destructor">
<emphasis box="[426,575,1584,1611]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">O. destructor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Weksler, M. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R." box="[617,960,1584,1611]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="417 - 437" refId="ref75717" refString="Weksler, M. &amp; Bonvicino, C. R. (2015 b) Genus Oligoryzomys Bangs, 1900. In: Patton, J., Pardinas, U. F. J. &amp; D'Elia, G. (Eds.), Mammals of South America. 2. Rodents. University of Chicago Press, Chicago, Illinois, pp. 417 - 437." type="book chapter" year="2015">Weksler &amp; Bonvicino (2015b)</bibRefCitation>
. However, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Hurtado, N. &amp; D'Elia, G." pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="127 - 144" refId="ref68090" refString="Hurtado, N. &amp; D'Elia, G. (2019 b) Taxonomy of the long-tailed mouse Oligoryzomys destructor (Sigmodontinae: Oryzomyini) with the designation of neotypes for Hesperomys destructor Tschudi, 1844 and Hesperomys melanostoma Tschudi, 1844. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 57 (1), 127 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jzs. 12232" type="journal article" year="2019">Hurtado &amp; D’Elía (2019b)</bibRefCitation>
, the authors taken these values arbitrary from 
<bibRefCitation author="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L." box="[784,1076,1620,1647]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref67114" refString="Gardner, A. L. &amp; Patton, J. L. (1976) Karyotypic variation in Oryzomyine rodents (Cricetinae) with comments on chromosomal evolution in the Neotropical Cricetine complex. Occasional papers of the Museum of Zoology, 49, 1 - 48." type="journal article" year="1976">Gardner &amp; Patton (1976)</bibRefCitation>
, whom described at least three karyotypes for specimens from localities in the current known distribution of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tschudi" baseAuthorityYear="1844" box="[1048,1200,1656,1683]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Oligoryzomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="destructor">
<emphasis box="[1048,1200,1656,1683]" italics="true" pageId="60" pageNumber="61">O. destructor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Consequently, such specimens should be revised in order to confirm the karyotype of this species (
<bibRefCitation author="Hurtado, N. &amp; D'Elia, G." box="[1030,1317,1692,1719]" pageId="60" pageNumber="61" pagination="127 - 144" refId="ref68090" refString="Hurtado, N. &amp; D'Elia, G. (2019 b) Taxonomy of the long-tailed mouse Oligoryzomys destructor (Sigmodontinae: Oryzomyini) with the designation of neotypes for Hesperomys destructor Tschudi, 1844 and Hesperomys melanostoma Tschudi, 1844. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 57 (1), 127 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jzs. 12232" type="journal article" year="2019">Hurtado &amp; D’Elía 2019b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
